(73, 85, 0, 36, 'Grosvenor Black/ Grosvenor White/ Grosvenor Border / Grosvenor Porcelain/ Grosvenor Outdoor Tiles'),
(74, 75, 0, 37, 'London\'s Grosvenor House Hotel is known for its luxurious aesthetic and timeless styling, especially that of the Great Room, that was famously used for the world’s oldest charitable ball, the Royal Caledonian Ball. Bring a touch of the same classic opulence to your home décor with the Grosvenor™ black and white tile range. These square corner tiles coordinate perfectly with border and central tiles to provide a professional finishing touch to your tiling project.\nProduct Code: 630371\nProduct Colour: Black, White, Patterned, Multicoloured\nTile Surface: Floor, Wall\nTile Size: 11cm x 11cm Square\nTile Depth (cm): 0.83'),
(75, 76, 0, 37, 'Grosvenor™'),
(76, 85, 0, 37, 'Grosvenor Black/ Grosvenor White/ Grosvenor Corner / Grosvenor Porcelain/ Grosvenor Outdoor Tiles'),
(77, 75, 0, 38, 'Restoring the original flooring found in a Victorian property can be difficult, often the floor has been cracked with time or damaged from adhesives used to lay other flooring over the top from past eras. Coming across the original flooring to find replacements is also a costly venture, not only to source but to get fitted too.\n\nOur Victorian Flooring range has been specifically designed to replicate the traditional tile designs from the Victorian era but with a contemporary twist to keep your space feeling fresh and modern. From exquisite floor tiles to intricate border and corner pieces, its innovative mesh backing means easy and accurate installation every time, saving both time and money compared to individual tile installation.\n\nThe diamond border and corner pieces provide a classic touch to your Victorian Flooring, creating beautifully detailed edging to equal your statement floor.\nProduct Code: 690137\nProduct Colour: Patterned\nTile Surface: Floor\nTile Size: 9.3cm x 9.3cm Corner\nTile Depth (cm): 0.83'),
